This paper discusses evolutionary multiobjective optimization (EMO) algorithms, which are commonly used in the field of computational intelligence. The paper specifically addresses the issue of scaling EMO algorithms for problems with many objectives, which is a common problem in the field of machine learning and optimization. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
